{{Infobox software | name = Matija | logo = [[File:SDlogo color.gif|alt=SmartDraw logo]] | caption = SmartDraw | developer = SmartDraw, LLC | genre = Diagramming software | latest_release_version = SmartDraw and SmartDraw for Windows Desktop | latest_release_date = April 2018 | operating_system = [[MacOS|Mac]], [[Windows Vista|Vista]], [[Windows 7]], [[Windows 10]] | license = [[Proprietary software|Proprietary]] | website = {{url|https://www.smartdraw.com}} |}}
'''SmartDraw''' is a diagram tool used to make [[flowcharts]], [[org chart|organization charts]], [[mind maps]], [[gantt charts|project charts]], and other business visuals. SmartDraw has two versions: an online edition and a downloadable edition for Windows desktop.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eetimes.com/author.asp?section_id=36&doc_id=1284975|title=SmartDraw – The Visio Killer?|date=February 3, 2011|website=EETimes|language=en-US|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.business.com/reviews/smartdraw/|title=SmartDraw Review|date=December 18, 2017|website=Business.com|language=en-US|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Thomas F. Goldman|title=SmartDraw: A Hands-on Tutorial and Guide |url=https://books.google.rs/books?id=2q61OwAACAAJ&dq=SmartDraw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwioy86zjpLeAhWEkZAKHQNFAl0Q6AEINzAC |publisher=Prentice Hall|date= 2009 |isbn=0135064341}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Daniel G. Hoffmann, Doug Lowe|title=SmartDraw For Dummies |url=https://books.google.rs/books?id=rEuoNqr6oa4C&printsec=frontcover&dq=SmartDraw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwioy86zjpLeAhWEkZAKHQNFAl0Q6AEIMDAB#v=onepage&q=SmartDraw&f=false |publisher=John Wiley & Sons|date= April 29, 2009 |isbn=047052488X}}</ref>
==Integration and Add-Ons== SmartDraw integrates with [[Microsoft Office]] products including [[Word]], [[PowerPoint]], and [[Microsoft Excel|Excel]] and G Suite applications like Google Docs and Google Sheets.
SmartDraw also has apps for Atlassian's Confluence, Jira, and Trello.
SmartDraw is compatible with Google Drive, Dropbox, Box, and OneDrive.
